args: I can't see anything.\nAh. So I've died...
I have no regrets. I swore to protect the\npeople at the cost of my own life, and I\nhave seen that oath through. My death is—
Good. Now this armor should allow the\nwearer to withstand the otherworld.
I have to say, making something like this\nfor myself really highlights what a genius\nshe was.
(So she too had someone important\nto her.)
Just how much time has passed since you\nleft this world?
My name, my home... I've given up so\nmuch to keep protecting this world you\nfought for.
And I would do it all again. But the one\nthing I was never able to truly let go of...\nwas you.
I only made this so that I could search for\nyou beyond the otherworld gate.
I want to see you again. I broke my wings,\ntook on a new identity...but that single\nthought has never left me.
And yet I can't leave.\nNot after assuming my vigil.
In becoming mother to all, I have failed\nto mother the one who matters most: you.
(Her thoughts and emotions are flooding\ninto me. Her grief wrenches my insides.\nBut...there's something more?)
I've been thinking ever since. I believe that\nthe choice you made was the right one.\nBut it wasn't what I'd wanted.
At the time, you had no choice but to\nsacrifice yourself, but if some alternative\nhad existed, I'd want you to take it.
So I've decided to pass on this armor I\nmade to search for you. To protect the\nworld—to protect my beloved children.
In the hopes that someone who feels\nas you did will tread the path you were\ndenied!
Sacrificing yourself for the ones you love\nmay be noble, but I still wish for you to\nchoose a path where you live on.
(A path of life, instead of sacrifice...)
Love is aught given to others, Tobias. Think\nnot of yourself, but dedicate all your heart\nand all your might to others' happiness.
In time, that love will find its way back\nto you. To love one's neighbor is to love\noneself. So never forget this lesson.
The Goddess does not ask for you to make\na sacrifice of yourself. For you are as much\nHer beloved child as any other.
(Father... You taught me this lesson from\nan early age, but only now do I truly\nunderstand its meaning.)
I will no longer be led by the hand like\na child. My job now is to guide.
I shall leave the perditionists to you,\nTobias.
(Elisanne... Though our beliefs and\nmethods differ, we swore to give our all\nto accomplish the same goal.)
I'm not an object in need of protection\nanymore. I'll overcome what troubles\nthe future may bring myself.
I want to travel. To see the world with my\nown two eyes.
Let me return the gem that forms this\narmor to you. It was a charm handed\ndown for your protection.
No. You keep it. I don't think I'm really\nbuilt to wear armor. Plus...
I'm sure my ancestors would rather it be\nused in the fight for a happier world.
(I swore to Nino I would give my all to\nprotect the people's happiness when I\naccepted that charm from her.)
(All along, I had a cause to fight for.\nA reason I can't afford to die.)
I want to protect you because I love you.\nYou, and this world. So I want you to live.
May you give all your heart and all\nyour might to protect all of my beloved\nchildren...including yourself.
(So this is the true desire she imbued this\narmor with. If I'm to live up to that wish,\neven a little longer, I—!)
